plot: The amazing career of master magician Harry Houdini is presented from his beginnings with a carnival &"wild man&" act to his emergence as an internationally-acclaimed illusionist, From his mysterious escape from a locked safe under the frozen Detroit River to dramatic one from a locked cell in Scotland Yard, he never failed to please his audience. Although Houdini's tricks are achieved through a marvelous physical dexterity and innate sleight-of-hand, he courted death with the hazardous illusions he performed and his compulsive quest to contact the spirit world.   Written by  duke1029@aol.com
title: El gran Houdini
